# Constants and Types Rules

## Constants
- All constants MUST be in `lib/constants/` directory
- Use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for constant names
- Group related constants in the same file:
  - Profile types: `lib/constants/profile-types.ts`
  - Content types: `lib/constants/content-types.ts`
  - Status options: `lib/constants/status-options.ts`
  - Filter options: `lib/constants/filter-options.ts`
  - Roles: `lib/constants/roles.ts`

## Types
- All shared types MUST be in `lib/types/` directory
- Display types go in `lib/types/display.ts`
- API types go in `lib/types/api.ts`
- Component types go in `lib/types/components.ts`
- Component-specific props can stay in component files if only used once

## Labels and Options
- Labels (e.g., `PROFILE_TYPE_LABELS`, `ROLE_LABELS`) should be constants
- Select options (e.g., `STATUS_FILTER_OPTIONS`) should be constants
- NO inline label objects or option arrays in components

## Import Rules
- Always import constants from `lib/constants/`
- Always import types from `lib/types/`
- Always import utils from `lib/utils/`
- Use absolute imports with `@/` prefix
